# gen106 (L1) — the bilingual ratchet (LOOP.md). The learned end-of-sequence is
# structural, not lexical: the SAME boundary induction and decode loop read
# Italian text. "dorme" ends the utterance twice and continues to "sul letto"
# once, so the model halts after "dorme" — a learned EOS, in Italian, through the
# identical code path. No phrasebook, no duplicated logic.

> learn sequence: il gatto dorme . il gatto dorme . il gatto dorme sul letto .
< Learned 8 transition(s).
> say il
< il gatto dorme